{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"birch-argon-mouse","description":"## Why\nThe additive model and its back-compat/lifecycle invariants must be locked by tests.\n## What\nCover: plan-review then close retains BOTH attestations; re-running a kind replaces only\nthat kind; round-trip through compaction preserves all kinds; a legacy single-signature\nticket (and an old-clone SNAPSHOT carrying only `signature`) still reads and verifies via\nfold-in; reopening a closed ticket makes completion read as not-valid while leaving the\nrecord intact; concurrent signs of different kinds both survive.\n## Scope\n`tests/interfaces/lifecycle/` (attestation coexistence, reopen validity), reducer/compaction\nunit tests, `tests/unit/test_signing.py`.\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Test: plan-review + close retains both kinds; re-sign a kind replaces in place.\n- [ ] Test: compaction/SNAPSHOT round-trip preserves all kinds.\n- [ ] Test: legacy single-signature ticket + old-clone snapshot read/verify via fold-in.\n- [ ] Test: reopen makes completion read not-valid; record unchanged; re-close re-signs.\n- [ ] Test: concurrent different-kind signs both survive (per-key LWW convergence).","id":"dbe6-314c-2aad-493a","parent_id":"4702-a55c-7aeb-445a","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Tests: coexistence, compaction, legacy read, reopen validity"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782782726271585001,"uuid":"7df93089-a05f-4ca1-b491-4f75ba1e6135"}